1
00:00:24,483 --> 00:00:26,683
I'm talkin'about friendship.

2
00:00:26,583 --> 00:00:29,183
I'm talkin'about character.

3
00:00:29,483 --> 00:00:33,683
I'm talkin'about--
Hell, Leo, I ain't embarrassed
to use the word.

4
00:00:33,883 --> 00:00:36,883
I'm talkin' about ethics.

5
00:00:37,183 --> 00:00:39,183
You know I'm a sportin' man.

6
00:00:39,283 --> 00:00:41,683
I like to lay the occasional bet.

7
00:00:41,783 --> 00:00:44,283
But I ain't that sportin'.

8
00:00:44,483 --> 00:00:47,283
When I fix a fight--
Say I pay a three to one favorite...

9
00:00:47,383 --> 00:00:49,383
to throw a goddamned fight.

10
00:00:49,483 --> 00:00:53,483
I figure I got the right
to expect that fight
to go off at three to one.

11
00:00:53,783 --> 00:00:57,283
But every time I lay in bed
with this son of a bitch
Bernie Bernbaum,

12
00:00:57,483 --> 00:01:00,683
before I know it,
the odds is even up.

13
00:01:00,883 --> 00:01:03,383
Or worse, I'm bettin'
on the short money.

14
00:01:03,583 --> 00:01:05,683
The sheeny knows
I like sure things.

15
00:01:05,883 --> 00:01:09,183
He's sellin' the information
I fixed the fight.

16
00:01:09,383 --> 00:01:11,683
Out of town money
comes pouring in.

17
00:01:11,783 --> 00:01:13,983
The odds go straight to hell.

18
00:01:14,183 --> 00:01:17,383
I don't know who
he's sellin' to-- maybe
the Los Angeles combine.

19
00:01:17,483 --> 00:01:19,383
I don't know. The point is,

20
00:01:19,583 --> 00:01:23,583
Bernie ain't satisfied
with the honest dollar
he can make off the vig.

21
00:01:23,783 --> 00:01:26,883
He ain't satisfied with
the business I do on his book.

22
00:01:27,083 --> 00:01:29,883
He is sellin' tips on how I bet.

23
00:01:30,083 --> 00:01:33,183
And that means part
of the payoff that should
be riding on my hip...

24
00:01:33,383 --> 00:01:35,383
is riding on someone else's.

25
00:01:35,583 --> 00:01:37,983
So, back we go
to these questions--

26
00:01:38,183 --> 00:01:41,883
friendship, character,

27
00:01:42,183 --> 00:01:44,383
ethics.

28
00:01:47,583 --> 00:01:49,583
So, it's clear what I'm saying?

29
00:01:51,083 --> 00:01:53,783
As mud.

30
00:01:56,583 --> 00:02:02,083
It's gettin' so a businessman
can't expect no return
from a fixed fight.

31
00:02:02,383 --> 00:02:05,683
Now, if you can't trust a fix,
what can you trust?

32
00:02:05,883 --> 00:02:09,083
For a good return,you gotta
go bettin'on chance,

33
00:02:09,383 --> 00:02:11,483
and then you're
back with anarchy.

34
00:02:11,683 --> 00:02:13,483
Right back in the jungle.

35
00:02:13,683 --> 00:02:18,583
That's why ethics is important--
what separates us
from the animals,

36
00:02:18,783 --> 00:02:21,183
the beasts of burden,
the beasts of prey.

37
00:02:21,383 --> 00:02:23,283
Ethics.

38
00:02:23,383 --> 00:02:27,383
Whereas, uh, Bernie Bernbaum
is a horse of a different color,

39
00:02:27,583 --> 00:02:31,183
ethics-wise, as in
he ain't got any.

40
00:02:31,483 --> 00:02:35,383
- You sure it's Bernie
selling you out?
- It ain't elves.

41
00:02:35,683 --> 00:02:39,383
- No one else knows about the fix?
- No one that ain't got ethics.

42
00:02:39,483 --> 00:02:42,383
What about the fighters
you pay to tank out?

43
00:02:42,683 --> 00:02:46,483
We only pick fighters
we know we can put
the fear of God in.

44
00:02:46,683 --> 00:02:48,883
Any other bookies know?
You play anyone else's book?

45
00:02:48,983 --> 00:02:52,083
I-I lay an occasional bet
with Mink Larouie.

46
00:02:52,383 --> 00:02:54,783
- But it ain't Mink.
I'll vouch for that.
-How do you know?

47
00:02:54,983 --> 00:02:58,083
It ain't Mink.
Mink is Eddie Dane's boy.

48
00:02:58,283 --> 00:03:01,983
Of course the Dane
always knows about the fix.

49
00:03:02,183 --> 00:03:04,283
And what the hell
is that supposed to mean?

50
00:03:04,483 --> 00:03:07,783
Let it drift. All it means is
a lot of people know.

51
00:03:07,983 --> 00:03:10,283
I guess you ain't
been listenin'.

52
00:03:10,383 --> 00:03:12,483
Sure, other people know.

53
00:03:12,683 --> 00:03:15,283
That's why we gotta go
to this question of character...

54
00:03:15,483 --> 00:03:18,983
to determine just who, exactly,
is chiselin' in on my fix.

55
00:03:19,283 --> 00:03:22,883
And that's how we know
that it's Bernie Bernbaum,
the shmatte kid--

56
00:03:23,083 --> 00:03:25,983
'cause ethically,
he's kinda shaky.

57
00:03:27,383 --> 00:03:31,283
- So you want to kill him.
- For starters.

58
00:03:45,983 --> 00:03:50,283
Sorry, Caspar.
Bernie pays for protection.

59
00:03:51,983 --> 00:03:54,983
Listen, Leo, I ain't
askin' you for permission.

60
00:03:55,183 --> 00:03:59,183
I'm tellin' you as a courtesy.
I need to do this thing,
so it's gonna get done.

61
00:03:59,483 --> 00:04:01,283
And I'm tellin' you, as
a courtesy, you'll have trouble.

62
00:04:01,483 --> 00:04:05,183
You came here to see if
I'd kick if you killed Bernie.
Well, there's your answer.

63
00:04:05,383 --> 00:04:08,983
I pay off to you every month
like a greengrocer

64
00:04:09,083 --> 00:04:10,983
a lot more than the shmatte,

65
00:04:11,183 --> 00:04:13,083
and I'm sick of gettin'
the high hat.

66
00:04:13,183 --> 00:04:16,083
You pay off for protection
just like everyone else.

67
00:04:16,283 --> 00:04:18,983
As far as I know, and
what I don't know in this town
ain't worth knowing,

68
00:04:19,183 --> 00:04:21,083
the cops haven't closed
any of your dives...

69
00:04:21,183 --> 00:04:23,583
and the D.A. hasn't touched
any of your rackets.

70
00:04:23,783 --> 00:04:26,183
You haven't bought any license
to kill bookies,

71
00:04:26,383 --> 00:04:28,283
and today I ain't sellin'any.

72
00:04:28,483 --> 00:04:31,283
So take your flunky and dangle.

73
00:04:31,383 --> 00:04:35,683
You think I'm some guinea
fresh off the boat,
and you can kick me.

74
00:04:35,883 --> 00:04:39,783
But I'm too big for that now.
I'm sick of takin'
the strap from you, Leo.

75
00:04:40,083 --> 00:04:42,383
I'm sick of marching
into this goddamn office...

76
00:04:42,483 --> 00:04:44,483
to kiss your Irish ass,

77
00:04:44,583 --> 00:04:46,983
and I'm sick of the high hat!

78
00:05:03,783 --> 00:05:06,883
You's fancy pants, all of youse.

79
00:05:08,883 --> 00:05:11,283
Johnny?

80
00:05:11,483 --> 00:05:14,683
You're exactly as big
as I let you be and no bigger,

81
00:05:14,783 --> 00:05:16,983
and don't forget it, ever.

82
00:05:19,683 --> 00:05:21,583
That's right, Leo.

83
00:05:21,683 --> 00:05:23,683
You're the big shot
around here,

84
00:05:23,883 --> 00:05:27,383
and I'm just some schnook
likes to get slapped around.

85
00:05:34,983 --> 00:05:37,883
Twist a pig's ear,
watch him squeal.

86
00:05:46,583 --> 00:05:49,983
- Bad play, Leo.
- Who got up the wrong side, huh?

87
00:05:50,283 --> 00:05:52,983
-Same side as always.
- That's what I mean.
Still owe money to--

88
00:05:53,083 --> 00:05:56,483
Who is your bookie, Lazarre?
I could put it right for you.

89
00:05:56,683 --> 00:05:59,583
- Thanks, Leo. I don't need it.
- In a pig's eye.

90
00:05:59,783 --> 00:06:01,683
You haven't played
a winner in six weeks.

91
00:06:01,783 --> 00:06:04,083
People will speak ill of me
if I let him break your legs.

92
00:06:04,283 --> 00:06:07,983
- People will say I had it coming.
-And they'll be right,
but that ain't the point.

93
00:06:08,183 --> 00:06:11,883
Call me a bighearted slob,
but I'm gonna square it
for you, yeah.

94
00:06:12,183 --> 00:06:15,483
I think I'll do that
this very same night.

95
00:06:15,583 --> 00:06:19,383
Lookin' at you mopin' around
takes away all my--

96
00:06:19,583 --> 00:06:22,083
What do you call it?
"Joy de veever"?

97
00:06:22,283 --> 00:06:25,283
-Joie de vivre.
- Well, if you're gonna
laugh at me, the hell with ya.

98
00:06:25,383 --> 00:06:27,883
The hell with you.

99
00:06:28,183 --> 00:06:30,483
I'll square myself with Lazarre,
if you don't mind.

100
00:06:30,683 --> 00:06:33,483
That's why God invented cards.

101
00:06:36,083 --> 00:06:38,783
- There is one thing
you can do for me.
- Name it.

102
00:06:38,983 --> 00:06:41,283
Think about what
protecting Bernie gets us.

103
00:06:41,483 --> 00:06:43,983
Think about what
offending Caspar loses us.

104
00:06:44,183 --> 00:06:46,383
Oh, come on, Tommy.
You know I don't like to think.

105
00:06:46,583 --> 00:06:48,583
Yeah.

106
00:06:48,783 --> 00:06:52,583
Well, think about
whether you should start.

107
00:08:37,183 --> 00:08:39,383
Wake up, Tommy.

108
00:08:39,583 --> 00:08:42,583
- I am awake.
- Your eyes are shut.

109
00:08:42,683 --> 00:08:44,883
Who you gonna believe?

110
00:08:55,483 --> 00:08:58,083
- How'd I do?
- What do you think?

111
00:08:58,183 --> 00:09:00,883
You are a millionaire.
You gonna remember your friends?

112
00:09:04,383 --> 00:09:07,983
- Where's me hat?
- You bet it, mug.

113
00:09:08,083 --> 00:09:11,483
Good thing the game broke up
before you bet your trousers.

114
00:09:12,883 --> 00:09:15,983
- Who made off with me hat?

115
00:09:16,283 --> 00:09:18,983
Verna. Verna and Mink.

116
00:09:19,083 --> 00:09:21,383
- Who?
- Mink and Verna.

117
00:09:29,283 --> 00:09:31,483
Is Thunderclap running tonight?

118
00:09:31,683 --> 00:09:34,783
Thunderclap?
Yeah.

119
00:09:35,083 --> 00:09:36,983
What's she leaving at?

120
00:09:37,083 --> 00:09:39,583
Three to one, more than likely.

121
00:09:39,883 --> 00:09:42,983
Lay off, Tom. You shouldn't go
deeper in the hole.

122
00:09:43,183 --> 00:09:45,583
Tell Lazarre...

123
00:09:45,783 --> 00:09:49,083
I want 500 on the nose.

124
00:09:49,283 --> 00:09:51,683
You would have it.

125
00:10:04,783 --> 00:10:07,383
I want me hat.

126
00:10:07,483 --> 00:10:11,183
Is that all you came for?

127
00:10:11,383 --> 00:10:13,683
Yeah. I want me hat.

128
00:10:13,783 --> 00:10:15,883
It's mine. I won it.

129
00:10:15,983 --> 00:10:18,583
- What are you gonna do with it?
- Drop dead.

130
00:10:27,183 --> 00:10:29,983
I need a drink.

131
00:10:30,183 --> 00:10:32,683
Why didn't you say so?

132
00:11:29,283 --> 00:11:32,183
Hello, Tommy.
Sorry about the hour.

133
00:11:32,383 --> 00:11:36,083
- I'll live. What's the rumpus?
-Can I come in?

134
00:11:38,783 --> 00:11:41,283
Sure.

135
00:11:49,983 --> 00:11:52,983
- Drink?
- I wouldn't mind.

136
00:11:59,983 --> 00:12:01,983
I tried callin' earlier.

137
00:12:02,183 --> 00:12:04,683
I got home late.

138
00:12:10,083 --> 00:12:15,283
- Well, uh, I'm sorry about the hour.
- Uh-huh.

139
00:12:27,783 --> 00:12:31,283
- Not bad.
- Better than the paint
we sell at the club.

140
00:12:31,383 --> 00:12:33,983
That it is. That it is.

141
00:12:37,683 --> 00:12:39,783
- You thought about
cutting Bernie loose?
- Can't do it, Tommy.

142
00:12:39,983 --> 00:12:42,783
Can't do it.

143
00:12:42,983 --> 00:12:45,383
That's sort of why I'm, uh--

144
00:12:48,083 --> 00:12:50,983
Tommy, I don't know where Verna is.

145
00:12:51,283 --> 00:12:54,483
- Uh-huh.
- I know what you're thinkin',
what else is new?

146
00:12:54,683 --> 00:12:57,483
But the situation now--
I'm worried.

147
00:12:57,683 --> 00:13:00,983
Verna can take care of herself,
maybe better than you can.

148
00:13:01,283 --> 00:13:04,683
- What does that mean?
- Want another one?

149
00:13:04,883 --> 00:13:06,683
No.

150
00:13:06,883 --> 00:13:08,883
What does that mean?

151
00:13:08,983 --> 00:13:11,283
How far she got
her hooks into you?

152
00:13:11,483 --> 00:13:13,483
That's a hell of a question.

153
00:13:15,783 --> 00:13:17,883
It's a grift.

154
00:13:18,083 --> 00:13:21,583
If she didn't need you
to protect her brother
from Johnny Caspar,

155
00:13:21,783 --> 00:13:25,283
you think she'd still be going
on slow carriage rides with you
through the park?

156
00:13:25,583 --> 00:13:29,783
That's the deal, isn't it?
You keep Bernie under wraps
till Caspar cools down?

157
00:13:30,083 --> 00:13:33,783
Jesus, you're a prickly pear.
What's wrong with her wanting
her brother taken care of?

158
00:13:33,883 --> 00:13:35,783
Nothing. I don't blame her.

159
00:13:35,983 --> 00:13:38,183
She sees the angle,
which is you, she plays it.

160
00:13:38,383 --> 00:13:41,183
She's a grifter,
just like her brother.

161
00:13:41,383 --> 00:13:43,583
Probably had grifter parents
and grifter grandparents...

162
00:13:43,683 --> 00:13:46,683
and someday they're each
gonna spawn little grifter kids.

163
00:13:46,883 --> 00:13:49,983
Stop it, Tommy.
I don't like to hear my friends
run down, even by other friends.

164
00:13:50,183 --> 00:13:52,283
- Friendship's got
nothing to do with it.
- The hell you say.

165
00:13:52,483 --> 00:13:55,183
You'd do anything to help
your friends, like you'd do
anything to kick your enemies.

166
00:13:55,283 --> 00:13:56,783
- Wrong, Leo.
You do things for a reason.
- Okay, Tom.

167
00:13:56,883 --> 00:13:58,783
- Wrong, Leo.
You do things for a reason.
- Okay, Tom.

168
00:13:58,883 --> 00:14:01,883
You know all the angles,
Christ, better than anybody.

169
00:14:04,083 --> 00:14:07,183
But maybe you're wrong
about this. You don't know
what's in Verna's heart.

170
00:14:07,383 --> 00:14:10,083
Leo, if she's such an angel,

171
00:14:10,283 --> 00:14:12,383
why are you looking for her
at 4:00 in the morning?

172
00:14:16,983 --> 00:14:18,783
I put a tail on her this afternoon.

173
00:14:20,283 --> 00:14:24,683
- Uh-huh.
- I asked Rug Daniels
to follow her around,

174
00:14:24,983 --> 00:14:28,083
just, you know,
to keep her out of trouble.

175
00:14:28,283 --> 00:14:32,283
I was worried.
After that meeting with Caspar,
you can't be too careful.

176
00:14:32,483 --> 00:14:35,583
- So what did Rug say that has you
scurrying over here?
- That's just it.

177
00:14:35,883 --> 00:14:41,283
- Nothing. He's disappeared.
- So you lost your lady friend
and the tail you put on her?

178
00:14:41,583 --> 00:14:44,083
I guess it does sound
pretty sorry at that.

179
00:14:44,283 --> 00:14:47,583
Help me out, Tom.
I wouldn't know where
to start lookin'.

180
00:14:47,883 --> 00:14:50,283
You know Rug's crowd.
You know the people Verna runs with.

181
00:14:50,483 --> 00:14:53,983
It's just I'm worried now
with things the way they are
between me and Caspar.

182
00:14:54,083 --> 00:14:56,883
You shouldn't be confronting
Johnny Caspar. That's what
I've been trying to tell you.

183
00:14:56,983 --> 00:14:59,783
You can't trade
body blows with him.
He's gotten too strong.

184
00:14:59,983 --> 00:15:03,883
I reckon I can still trade body blows
with any man in this town.

185
00:15:08,083 --> 00:15:10,683
Except you, Tom.

186
00:15:10,883 --> 00:15:12,783
And Verna.

187
00:15:22,783 --> 00:15:25,283
Okay. Give me the needle.

188
00:15:27,283 --> 00:15:30,283
I am a sap.

189
00:15:30,483 --> 00:15:33,683
I deserve it.

190
00:15:33,983 --> 00:15:35,983
Thanks for the drink.

191
00:15:37,483 --> 00:15:39,683
Let me know
if you hear anything.

192
00:16:08,383 --> 00:16:11,783
- Who was that?
- Leo.

193
00:16:11,983 --> 00:16:14,083
He's lookin' for you.

194
00:16:14,283 --> 00:16:16,683
Did you tell him I was here?

195
00:16:16,783 --> 00:16:19,183
No.

196
00:16:21,783 --> 00:16:24,983
Did you put in a good word
for my brother?

197
00:16:25,283 --> 00:16:27,283
No.

198
00:16:27,483 --> 00:16:30,583
- You said you would.
- I said I'd think about it.

199
00:16:32,783 --> 00:16:34,883
What did you tell him?

200
00:16:37,983 --> 00:16:40,683
Did you see
Rug Daniels last night?

201
00:16:40,883 --> 00:16:43,183
No.

202
00:16:43,283 --> 00:16:45,283
What did you tell Leo?

203
00:16:45,483 --> 00:16:48,083
I told him you were a tramp
and he should dump you.

204
00:16:52,083 --> 00:16:54,883
You're a son of a bitch, Tom.

205
00:18:08,083 --> 00:18:10,183
- Hello, Tom.
What's the rumpus?
- Mink.

206
00:18:10,383 --> 00:18:12,383
- I see you got your hat back.
- Yeah, what of it?

207
00:18:12,483 --> 00:18:14,483
Not a thing. Look,
if it ain't my business,
I got not a thing to say.

208
00:18:14,683 --> 00:18:16,583
Listen, Bernie wants to see you.
It's important.

209
00:18:16,683 --> 00:18:18,583
Yeah, well, I'm right here.
I'm not made of glass.

210
00:18:18,783 --> 00:18:21,283
He's nervous walkin' around
in public. He's a right guy,
but he's very nervous.

211
00:18:21,483 --> 00:18:23,983
I mean, who wouldn't be?
In the spot he's in,
who wouldn't be?

212
00:18:24,083 --> 00:18:26,383
He asked me to ask you
to ask Leo to take care of him.

213
00:18:26,483 --> 00:18:28,483
Leo listens to you.
Not that Leo wouldn't help
a shmatte anyway.

214
00:18:28,683 --> 00:18:30,883
A guy like Bernie?
A straight shooter like him?

215
00:18:31,083 --> 00:18:33,683
- I don't get it, Mink.
- What's to get? It's as plain
as the nose on your face.

216
00:18:33,883 --> 00:18:36,083
- I thought you were
Eddie Dane's sycophant.
- Yeah, Tom, that's right,

217
00:18:36,283 --> 00:18:38,183
but a guy can have more
than one friend, can't he?

218
00:18:38,283 --> 00:18:41,283
Not that I want the Dane to know
about it, but the shmatte,
he's a right guy, Tommy.

219
00:18:41,483 --> 00:18:43,983
He's got a mixed reputation,
but for a sheeny, he's got
a lot of good qualities.

220
00:18:44,183 --> 00:18:47,283
- What's goin' on
between you and Bernie?
- Nothin', Tom.

221
00:18:47,483 --> 00:18:49,383
We're just...
friends, you know, amigos.

222
00:18:49,583 --> 00:18:51,883
You're a fickle boy, Mink.

223
00:18:51,983 --> 00:18:56,083
If Eddie Dane finds out
that you got another "amigo"--

224
00:18:56,383 --> 00:18:59,883
- Well, I don't peg him
for the understanding type.
- Find out?

225
00:19:00,183 --> 00:19:02,683
How's he gonna find out?
Damn it, you and me
ain't even been talkin'!

226
