- Yeah, .22.

443
00:34:13,583 --> 00:34:16,183
Listen, Tom, I'm just
the chief around here,

444
00:34:16,483 --> 00:34:18,483
so don't bother tellin' me
if you don't happen to
feel like it,

445
00:34:18,583 --> 00:34:20,383
but what the hell is Leo doin'?

446
00:34:20,583 --> 00:34:24,883
Make him listen to you, Tom.
It ain't right, all this fuss
over one sheeny.

447
00:34:25,083 --> 00:34:27,883
Let Caspar have Bernie.
What's one Hebrew more or less?

448
00:34:28,083 --> 00:34:29,983
We're burnin'
our meal ticket here.

449
00:34:30,083 --> 00:34:32,283
Leo will do what suits him,
and you'll do what he tells you.

450
00:34:32,383 --> 00:34:34,283
Last I heard, Leo was still
running this town.

451
00:34:34,483 --> 00:34:36,983
Yeah, well, he won't be
for long if this keeps up.

452
00:34:37,183 --> 00:34:39,783
It's no good for anyone.
You said as much yourself.

453
00:34:39,983 --> 00:34:43,983
First off, O'Doole, I can
say what I please to Leo
and about him.

454
00:34:44,283 --> 00:34:46,183
You can't.

455
00:34:46,383 --> 00:34:49,783
Second, once Leo decides,
that's that.

456
00:34:49,983 --> 00:34:52,283
If that sticks going down,
there are plenty
of coppers I know...

457
00:34:52,483 --> 00:34:55,183
who wouldn't mind
bein' chief and could
swallow it clean.

458
00:34:55,483 --> 00:34:59,383
Jesus, Tom,
I was just speculatin'
about a hypothesis.

459
00:34:59,583 --> 00:35:01,583
I know I don't
know nothin'.

460
00:35:01,683 --> 00:35:03,983
It's just a--
just a damn mess, is all.

461
00:35:28,383 --> 00:35:30,283
Hello, Officer. I'd like to
report an intruder...

462
00:35:30,383 --> 00:35:33,383
at 346 West Lewis--

463
00:35:33,483 --> 00:35:36,983
Who's this?
Hello, Shad. Tom Reagan here.

464
00:35:37,283 --> 00:35:39,883
- You need the booze?
- No, we won't be
needing any today.

465
00:35:40,083 --> 00:35:42,783
- False alarm, huh?
- Yeah. My mother.
She didn't recognize me.

466
00:35:42,983 --> 00:35:45,183
Let me talk to Mulveany.
Miss me?

467
00:35:45,383 --> 00:35:47,683
Drop dead.

468
00:35:47,883 --> 00:35:49,883
- Mulveany here.
- Sean?

469
00:35:49,983 --> 00:35:51,883
Tell O'Doole to get a car
over to Leo's tonight.

470
00:35:52,083 --> 00:35:54,883
If we're banging away
at Caspar, we oughta be ready
for him to bang back.

471
00:35:55,083 --> 00:35:57,183
-
- What do you want?

472
00:35:57,383 --> 00:36:00,983
I was in the neighborhood,
feeling a bit daffy,

473
00:36:01,283 --> 00:36:04,083
so I thought I'd drop in
for an aperitif.

474
00:36:05,983 --> 00:36:08,783
- Rug Daniels is dead.
- Gee, that's tough.

475
00:36:08,983 --> 00:36:11,083
Don't get hysterical.

476
00:36:11,283 --> 00:36:14,683
I've had enough excitement
for one night without a dame
going all weepy on me.

477
00:36:14,883 --> 00:36:16,883
- I barely knew the gentleman.
-Rug?

478
00:36:17,083 --> 00:36:21,283
A bit of a shakedown artist,
not above the occasional grift.

479
00:36:21,583 --> 00:36:25,183
Bet you'd understand that.
All in all, not a bad guy,

480
00:36:25,483 --> 00:36:28,683
if looks, brains
and personality don't count.

481
00:36:28,883 --> 00:36:31,483
- You better hope they don't.
- Yeah, well--

482
00:36:31,583 --> 00:36:34,083
We're none of us the saint
I hear your brother is.

483
00:36:34,283 --> 00:36:36,383
- Who killed him?
- Leo thinks Caspar did.

484
00:36:36,583 --> 00:36:38,483
- But you know better.
- I do now.

485
00:36:38,583 --> 00:36:41,783
You see, Caspar just tried
to buy me into fixing
his tiff with Leo,

486
00:36:41,983 --> 00:36:44,683
which he'd hardly do
if he was waging war.

487
00:36:44,883 --> 00:36:48,783
So I figure you killed him, angel.
You or St. Bernard.

488
00:36:48,883 --> 00:36:52,583
Why would I or my brother
kill Rug Daniels or anybody else?

489
00:36:52,783 --> 00:36:56,683
Rug was following you.
He knew about you and me,

490
00:36:56,983 --> 00:36:59,483
and that wouldn't help
your play with Leo, would it?

491
00:36:59,683 --> 00:37:01,683
You think I murdered someone?

492
00:37:01,883 --> 00:37:04,783
Come on, Tom.
You know me a little.

493
00:37:04,983 --> 00:37:07,383
Nobody knows anybody.
Not that well.

494
00:37:07,583 --> 00:37:09,683
You know, or you
wouldn't be here.

495
00:37:09,883 --> 00:37:13,083
Not at all, sugar.
I came to hear your side of the story.

496
00:37:13,283 --> 00:37:17,683
How horrible Rug was,
how he goaded you into it,
how he tried to shake you down.

497
00:37:17,983 --> 00:37:19,983
- That's not why
you came either.
- Tell me why I came.

498
00:37:20,183 --> 00:37:23,183
- The oldest reason there is.
- There are friendlier
places to drink.

499
00:37:23,383 --> 00:37:25,283
- Why can't you admit it?
- Admit what?

500
00:37:25,383 --> 00:37:28,583
That you don't like
me seeing Leo
'cause you're jealous.

501
00:37:28,783 --> 00:37:30,983
Admit that you've
got a heart,

502
00:37:31,183 --> 00:37:33,583
even though it may be
small and feeble...

503
00:37:33,683 --> 00:37:35,783
and you can't remember
the last time you used it.

504
00:37:35,983 --> 00:37:38,983
If I'd known we were gonna
cast our feelings into words,

505
00:37:39,183 --> 00:37:41,683
I'd have memorized
the Song of Solomon.

506
00:37:43,883 --> 00:37:46,983
Maybe that's why
I like you, Tom.

507
00:37:47,083 --> 00:37:49,783
I never knew anybody
that made being
a son of a bitch...

508
00:37:50,083 --> 00:37:52,683
such a point of pride.

509
00:37:52,783 --> 00:37:55,683
Though one day you'll
pay the price for it.

510
00:37:57,183 --> 00:38:00,883
Okay, Verna.
But until then, let's get stinko.

511
00:38:01,083 --> 00:38:03,483
Let's do something else first.

512
00:38:08,383 --> 00:38:10,683
Yeah. Let's do plenty.

513
00:42:08,183 --> 00:42:10,883
- Who's winning?
- We are, for the nonce.

514
00:42:10,983 --> 00:42:14,983
- What's the "disposish"?
- Last night, four to one. Dana
Cudahy went up with the house.

515
00:42:15,283 --> 00:42:17,383
- And theirs?
- One burned.

516
00:42:17,583 --> 00:42:19,283
- The other three?
- Lead.

517
00:42:19,383 --> 00:42:21,383
- Whose?
- Leo's.

518
00:42:21,483 --> 00:42:23,683
The old man's still
an artist with a Thompson.

519
00:42:23,883 --> 00:42:25,783
Yeah, do that.

520
00:42:25,783 --> 00:42:29,583
Well, find him, goddamn it!
Go and see if he fell in the john.

521
00:42:31,283 --> 00:42:34,083
Son of a bitch. No chief.

522
00:42:34,283 --> 00:42:37,483
- Who's mindin' the goddamn store?
-Can't raise O'Doole?

523
00:42:37,683 --> 00:42:39,683
No, nor the mayor either.

524
00:42:39,883 --> 00:42:44,083
- That's not good.
They're running.
- They wouldn't dare!

525
00:42:44,283 --> 00:42:46,883
I don't know, Leo.
I warned you not to
hit Caspar's club.

526
00:42:47,083 --> 00:42:49,783
- I'm still here, ain't I?
-Caspar's play hurt you anyway.

527
00:42:49,883 --> 00:42:52,283
That sorry son of a bitch
just slit his own throat.

528
00:42:52,483 --> 00:42:55,483
Listen to me, Leo.
Last night made you
look vulnerable.

529
00:42:55,783 --> 00:42:59,083
You don't hold elected office
in this town. You run it
because people think you run it.

530
00:42:59,183 --> 00:43:01,883
Once they stop thinking it,
you stop running it.

531
00:43:02,083 --> 00:43:05,283
Jesus, Tom. It sounds like
a bad break for me
I wasn't killed!

532
00:43:05,583 --> 00:43:08,483
I mean it, Leo.
Start taking Caspar seriously.

533
00:43:08,683 --> 00:43:12,783
I know, I know.
Retreat to win, give up Bernie.
That'll solve all our problems.

534
00:43:12,983 --> 00:43:14,983
Won't anymore, I'll grant you that.

535
00:43:15,183 --> 00:43:17,583
But going toe-to-toe
with a psychopath
will get you nowhere.

536
00:43:17,683 --> 00:43:20,283
It'll force people
to choose sides just when
you're looking shaky.

537
00:43:20,483 --> 00:43:23,583
- The hell I do!
- Then where's the mayor?

538
00:43:23,783 --> 00:43:25,983
Why aren't there
any police here?

539
00:43:26,083 --> 00:43:28,083
Why weren't there any police
at your place last night?

540
00:43:28,183 --> 00:43:30,683
- I didn't ask for any.
- I did.

541
00:43:33,983 --> 00:43:36,683
Mother hen, huh?
What's the matter, Tommy?

542
00:43:36,883 --> 00:43:40,283
- Don't you think
I can take care of myself?
- I know you can't.

543
00:43:40,483 --> 00:43:43,183
Here's the smart play, Leo.
You lay back, you give Bernie up,

544
00:43:43,383 --> 00:43:45,283
you let Caspar think
he's made his point.

545
00:43:45,483 --> 00:43:48,283
- Then you wait for him
to show a weakness.
- Please, Tom.

546
00:43:48,583 --> 00:43:50,683
You're sticking on Bernie.
You're sticking your neck out...

547
00:43:50,883 --> 00:43:53,683
for a guy who'd chop you off
at the heels if there
was two bits in it.

548
00:43:56,283 --> 00:43:58,883
Tom,

549
00:43:59,083 --> 00:44:02,283
things aren't as, uh,
clear-cut as you make it.

550
00:44:03,983 --> 00:44:07,983
Bernie's--
Well, hell,you know
about me and Verna.

551
00:44:08,183 --> 00:44:11,883
Things now are, uh--

552
00:44:12,083 --> 00:44:15,683
Not that I haven't
been a gentleman, but--

553
00:44:17,983 --> 00:44:21,283
I plan to ask her
to marry me, Tom.

554
00:44:26,083 --> 00:44:29,383
I guess you think
that's a bonehead play.

555
00:44:33,783 --> 00:44:37,383
- You think she wants you to?
- How the hell do I know?

556
00:44:37,683 --> 00:44:40,283
I think she does.
Yeah, of course she does.

557
00:44:40,483 --> 00:44:44,183
I know you think different,
but, well, we just, uh--

558
00:44:44,383 --> 00:44:46,683
We just differ on that.

559
00:44:49,583 --> 00:44:52,583
Leo, Caspar didn't kill Rug.

560
00:44:52,783 --> 00:44:56,383
- Course he did.
- No. Think about it
just this one time.

561
00:44:56,683 --> 00:44:58,583
- Who was Rug following?
- Huh?

562
00:44:58,783 --> 00:45:02,183
It needn't have been that
sinister. Strange man follows
her down a dark alleyway.

563
00:45:02,383 --> 00:45:04,683
- I told you she can
look after herself.
- Verna wouldn't panic,

564
00:45:04,783 --> 00:45:07,883
shoot someone just because
he was following her.

565
00:45:08,083 --> 00:45:11,683
Nah, it wouldn't have happened
like that, and if it had
she would have told me.

566
00:45:11,983 --> 00:45:15,083
They pulled a .22 slug out of him.
A pop gun, Leo, a woman's gun.

567
00:45:15,283 --> 00:45:17,383
I know you don't
like her, Tom,

568
00:45:17,483 --> 00:45:20,383
but I trust Verna
as much as I trust you.

569
00:45:22,083 --> 00:45:23,983
Okay, Leo.

570
00:45:24,083 --> 00:45:26,283
Maybe it wasn't that innocent.

571
00:45:26,483 --> 00:45:29,983
Maybe Rug knew something
she didn't like him knowing
and wouldn't want you to know.

572
00:45:30,283 --> 00:45:33,783
Rug was following her.
Maybe he knew
where she was sleeping,

573
00:45:33,983 --> 00:45:35,783
and who with.

574
00:45:39,983 --> 00:45:42,383
Maybes don't make it so.

575
00:45:43,583 --> 00:45:45,483
There's more than maybes.

576
00:45:45,683 --> 00:45:49,083
You've trusted me before,
you've never lost anything
by it. Trust me on this.

577
00:45:52,083 --> 00:45:55,383
- This is too important.
- I don't ask much,
and I don't ask often.

578
00:45:55,583 --> 00:45:57,883
Trust me on this.

579
00:45:58,083 --> 00:46:01,183
- Tommy.
- Trust me on this,
or to hell with you.

580
00:46:03,983 --> 00:46:06,183
You don't mean that.

581
00:46:09,183 --> 00:46:10,983
She was with me...

582
00:46:11,083 --> 00:46:14,383
the night Rug
was following her,

583
00:46:14,583 --> 00:46:16,483
the night you dropped by.

584
00:46:30,183 --> 00:46:32,483
Oh.

585
00:48:28,683 --> 00:48:31,383
Okay, Leo. Okay.
I'll throw him out.

586
00:48:33,583 --> 00:48:36,083
Yeah, do that.

587
00:48:37,283 --> 00:48:39,383
It's the kiss-off.

588
00:48:39,583 --> 00:48:42,783
If I never see him again,
it'll be soon enough.

589
00:48:53,183 --> 00:48:55,183
- Hello?
- Hello, Frankie.

590
00:48:55,283 --> 00:48:57,683
It's Tom.
How's the flunky business?

591
00:48:59,083 --> 00:49:01,283
I've had worse.
Your ventilator mending?

592
00:49:01,483 --> 00:49:04,483
-
- Tell Caspar it's forgotten.

593
00:49:04,683 --> 00:49:06,983
- I'd like to see him.

594
00:49:08,783 --> 00:49:10,883
Ah. All right, let me know.

595
00:49:56,283 --> 00:50:00,083
It worked, whatever you did.

596
00:50:00,383 --> 00:50:03,583
Leo says we're quits.

597
00:50:03,783 --> 00:50:06,383
But you know I didn't have
anything to do with Rug.

598
00:50:06,483 --> 00:50:09,183
Maybe not.

599
00:50:09,383 --> 00:50:11,283
Anyway, that isn't
what soured him on you.

600
00:50:11,483 --> 00:50:13,683
Oh, you and me, huh?

601
00:50:15,483 --> 00:50:18,983
You always take
the long way around to get
what you want, don't you, Tom?

602
00:50:21,283 --> 00:50:23,583
You could have just asked.

603
00:50:26,583 --> 00:50:29,383
What did I want?

604
00:50:29,583 --> 00:50:32,083
Me.

605
00:50:58,183 --> 00:51:00,883
Yeah?

606
00:51:00,983 --> 00:51:02,883
Yeah, yeah.

607
00:51:03,083 --> 00:51:05,283
When?

608
00:51:05,483 --> 00:51:07,283
Okay.

609
00:51:12,283 --> 00:51:14,883
You still up?

610
00:51:15,083 --> 00:51:17,183
Yeah.

611
00:51:21,083 --> 00:51:23,983
What are you chewin' over?

612
00:51:24,283 --> 00:51:26,383
Dream I had once.

613
00:51:28,383 --> 00:51:31,183
I was walking in the woods.
I don't know why.

614
00:51:32,883 --> 00:51:35,883
Wind came whippin'.
Blew me hat off.

615
00:51:37,983 --> 00:51:40,783
And you chased it, right?

616
00:51:40,983 --> 00:51:43,283
You ran and ran.

617
00:51:43,483 --> 00:51:46,483
You finally caught up to it.

618
00:51:46,783 --> 00:51:50,683
And you picked it up,
but it wasn't a hat anymore.

619
00:51:50,983 --> 00:51:54,783
It had changed into something else,
something wonderful.

620
00:51:54,883 --> 00:51:57,683
No, it stayed a hat.

621
00:51:57,783 --> 00:52:00,183
And no, I didn't chase it.

622
00:52:01,683 --> 00:52:05,383
Nothing more foolish
than a man chasin' his hat.

623
00:52:05,683 --> 00:52:07,783
Where are you going?

624
00:52:07,983 --> 00:52:10,583
Just have to do a few things.

625
00:52:10,783 --> 00:52:14,083
- You and Leo might still
be able to patch things up.
- Me and Leo are finished.

626
00:52:14,283 --> 00:52:17,583
-Nothing's gonna change that.
- You never know.

627
00:52:17,883 --> 00:52:21,483
- He's got a big heart.
- We're quits as far as I'm
concerned, never mind him.

628
00:52:21,683 --> 00:52:25,783
And if Leo did want me back,
he's an even bigger sap
than I thought.

629
00:52:26,083 --> 00:52:28,483
Then why don't we just
pick up and leave town?

630
00:52:28,583 --> 00:52:31,383
There's nothing keeping you here.

631
00:52:31,483 --> 00:52:33,383
I know there's nothing keeping me.

632
00:52:33,583 --> 00:52:36,783
- What about Bernie?
- He could go with us.

633
00:52:38,183 --> 00:52:40,183
You, me and Bernie?
Where would we go, Verna?

634
00:52:40,383 --> 00:52:42,283
Niagara Falls?

635
00:52:42,383 --> 00:52:44,283
Why do you hate him?

636
00:52:44,383 --> 00:52:46,283
- I don't hate anyone.
-Or like anyone.

637
00:52:51,383 --> 00:52:53,483
Where is Bernie?

638
00:52:53,583 --> 00:52:55,983
- Why?
- Leo can't protect him anymore.

639
00:52:56,183 --> 00:52:59,483
I oughta tell him to skip.

640
00:52:59,783 --> 00:53:01,583
The Royale, room 302.

641
00:53:06,983 --> 00:53:10,483
I guess we both
double-crossed Leo, huh?

642
00:53:10,683 --> 00:53:12,483
There's no gettin' around that.

643
00:53:13,783 --> 00:53:16,483
I guess he's well rid
of both of us.

644
00:53:16,683 --> 00:53:20,883
The two of us, we're about
bad enough to deserve each other.

645
00:53:24,483 --> 00:53:26,383
Are we?

646
00:53:28,583 --> 00:53:31,383
We're a couple of heels, Tom.

647
00:53:31,483 --> 00:53:34,083
Yes, we are.

648
00:53:34,383 --> 00:53:38,583
So he says,
"Screw him. Give him a dollar.
This was my idea. "

649
00:53:38,883 --> 00:53:42,383
Hello, Tom.

650
00:53:42,683 --> 00:53:45,783
Uh, you know O'Doole
and the mayor.

651
00:53:45,983 --> 00:53:49,083
- Hello, boys.
- Tom's a big booster.
Always has been.

652
00:53:49,283 --> 00:53:53,183
That's fine, that's fine.
Well, Tom and I got
the proverbial fat to chew.

653
00:53:53,483 --> 00:53:56,183
-Just let us know
if you need anything.
- Yeah. Happy days.

654
00:53:56,383 --> 00:53:59,283
Have a seat, kid.
Yeah, that's it.

655
00:53:59,583 --> 00:54:02,783
So,you had enough time
to think about things?

656
00:54:02,883 --> 00:54:06,883
- Yeah, well, uh,
circumstances have changed.
- Don't I know it.

657
00:54:07,083 --> 00:54:10,083
Last night I know the Dane
was disappointed
the bulls showed up...

658
00:54:10,283 --> 00:54:12,783
before Frankie and Tic-Tac
really pinned your ears back,

659
00:54:12,983 --> 00:54:17,283
but I said, "Relax, Eddie.
I got a feeling about this kid.

660
00:54:17,583 --> 00:54:21,583
The kid and Leo
are gonna go bust-o.
Matter of time."

661
00:54:21,883 --> 00:54:24,483
I said, "The kid
is too smart for Leo."
That's what I said.

662
00:54:24,583 --> 00:54:27,583
Like a psychic.
Ask the Dane if I did.
Like a goddamn psychic.

663
00:54:27,683 --> 00:54:30,083
-Go ahead, ask him.
- You vouch for that
psychic business?

664
00:54:30,283 --> 00:54:32,783
- That's right, smart guy.
-I know you knew...

665
00:54:32,883 --> 00:54:35,783
protecting the shmatte
was a dumb idea.

666
00:54:36,083 --> 00:54:39,683
I know you've been wise
to all of Leo's dumb ideas lately.

667
00:54:39,783 --> 00:54:41,883
Only a matter of time-- bust-o.

668
00:54:41,983 --> 00:54:45,083
That's why last night
we didn't put the arm on you,
only Leo.

