Because if you told me and I
killed you and you were lying,
I wouldn't get to kill you then.

894
01:09:50,383 --> 01:09:52,983
- Where's Leo?
- He's moving around.

895
01:09:53,183 --> 01:09:57,083
- He's getting his mob together
tomorrow at Whiskey Nick's.
- You sure?

896
01:09:57,383 --> 01:09:59,183
Check it. It's gold.

897
01:09:59,383 --> 01:10:02,883
You know what,yegg?
I believe you.

898
01:10:25,083 --> 01:10:27,083
Go ahead and run, sweetie.

899
01:10:27,283 --> 01:10:30,583
I'll track down
all of you whores.

900
01:11:30,983 --> 01:11:34,583
Hello, Bernie. Come on in.
Make yourself at home.

901
01:11:34,783 --> 01:11:37,683
Hello, Tom.

902
01:11:37,883 --> 01:11:41,483
I thought I'd do that,
since you didn't seem to be in.

903
01:11:41,783 --> 01:11:45,783
Figured it was a bad idea
to wait in the hall, seeing
as I'm supposed to be dead.

904
01:11:48,983 --> 01:11:51,383
How'd you know it was me?

905
01:11:51,483 --> 01:11:53,883
You're the only one I know
who'd knock and then break in.

906
01:11:54,083 --> 01:11:55,983
Your other friends
wouldn't break in?

907
01:11:56,183 --> 01:11:59,183
My other friends
want to kill me,
so they wouldn't knock.

908
01:11:59,383 --> 01:12:01,783
What's on your mind. Bernie?

909
01:12:04,283 --> 01:12:06,583
Things.

910
01:12:06,683 --> 01:12:11,983
I guess you must be angry.
I'm supposed to be
gone far away.

911
01:12:12,183 --> 01:12:15,183
I guess it seems sort of
irresponsible, my being here.

912
01:12:17,883 --> 01:12:21,283
And I was gonna leave.
Honest, I was.

913
01:12:21,383 --> 01:12:23,283
But then I started thinking...

914
01:12:23,483 --> 01:12:26,183
if I stuck around,
that would not be good for you.

915
01:12:26,383 --> 01:12:28,983
Then I started
thinking that--

916
01:12:29,183 --> 01:12:31,483
that might not
be bad for me.

917
01:12:34,883 --> 01:12:37,483
You didn't see
the play you gave me.

918
01:12:37,683 --> 01:12:39,883
I mean, what am I gonna do?

919
01:12:39,983 --> 01:12:42,783
If I leave, I got nothing.

920
01:12:42,983 --> 01:12:45,583
No money, no friends, nothing.

921
01:12:45,783 --> 01:12:47,883
If I stay, I got you.

922
01:12:47,983 --> 01:12:52,383
Anyone finds out I'm alive,
you're dead, so...

923
01:12:54,683 --> 01:12:56,683
I got-- I got you, Tommy.

924
01:12:59,283 --> 01:13:02,583
What's the matter?
You got nothing
to crack wise about?

925
01:13:02,683 --> 01:13:05,083
Bernie ain't
so funny anymore?

926
01:13:08,383 --> 01:13:11,183
I guess I made kind of
a fool of myself out there...

927
01:13:13,583 --> 01:13:15,983
bawling away like a twist.

928
01:13:16,183 --> 01:13:18,483
I guess--

929
01:13:18,683 --> 01:13:20,483
I guess I turned yellow.

930
01:13:20,683 --> 01:13:24,283
- You didn't tell anyone
about that?
- No.

931
01:13:24,383 --> 01:13:26,483
Of course,
you know about it.

932
01:13:30,583 --> 01:13:32,683
It's a painful memory...

933
01:13:34,583 --> 01:13:39,283
and I can't help remembering
that you put the finger on me,

934
01:13:39,483 --> 01:13:42,483
and you took me out there
to whack me.

935
01:13:42,783 --> 01:13:46,183
I know... you didn't.
I know.

936
01:13:46,383 --> 01:13:50,083
- You didn't shoot me, but--
- But what have I done
for you lately?

937
01:13:50,283 --> 01:13:52,283
Don't smart me.

938
01:13:53,883 --> 01:13:56,183
See, I want
to watch you squirm.

939
01:13:57,883 --> 01:14:00,283
I want to see you
sweat a little.

940
01:14:02,283 --> 01:14:04,283
And when you smart me...

941
01:14:05,883 --> 01:14:08,183
it ruins it.

942
01:14:18,083 --> 01:14:20,483
There's one other thing I want.

943
01:14:22,483 --> 01:14:25,183
I want to seeJohnny Caspar
cold and stiff.

944
01:14:25,283 --> 01:14:28,583
That's what you'll do
for your friend Bernie.

945
01:14:31,883 --> 01:14:34,983
In the meantime,
I'll stay out of sight.

946
01:14:35,183 --> 01:14:38,483
But if Caspar ain't stiff
in a couple of days...

947
01:14:38,683 --> 01:14:40,683
I start eating
in restaurants.

948
01:14:54,683 --> 01:14:56,783
Oof!.

949
01:15:00,783 --> 01:15:03,483
Uuh!

950
01:15:03,683 --> 01:15:05,683
You make me laugh, Tommy.

951
01:15:05,783 --> 01:15:09,283
You're gonna catch cold.
Then you're no good to me.

952
01:15:09,383 --> 01:15:12,183
What were you gonna do
if you caught me?

953
01:15:12,483 --> 01:15:15,783
I'd just squirt a few,
and then you'd let me go again.

954
01:15:22,883 --> 01:15:26,083
Hello, Tad.
How's the club holding up?

955
01:15:26,283 --> 01:15:29,783
We're managing to squeak by
without you.
Got Lazarre's money?

956
01:15:30,083 --> 01:15:33,083
- No.
- You're not supposed to be here
since you turned rat.

957
01:15:33,183 --> 01:15:35,683
Relax, Tad.
Leo isn't around, is he?

958
01:15:35,883 --> 01:15:39,783
Last couple of days you booked
any heavy bets on a long shot
at Saturday's fights?

959
01:15:40,083 --> 01:15:42,083
Why the hell
should I tell you?

960
01:15:42,183 --> 01:15:45,883
The truth is, Tad,
no reason on Earth.

961
01:15:48,683 --> 01:15:50,583
Saturday's fights?

962
01:15:50,683 --> 01:15:54,483
DropJohnson put two grand
on one yesterday--

963
01:15:54,783 --> 01:15:58,083
on Sailor Reese,
an undercard bum.

964
01:15:58,183 --> 01:16:01,183
DropJohnson.
He play your book much?

965
01:16:01,383 --> 01:16:04,583
- Are you kidding? I didn't
even know he could count.

966
01:16:04,783 --> 01:16:06,883
Jesus. You bring them with you?

967
01:16:07,083 --> 01:16:10,383
Hello, Brian.
Still fighting the good fight?

968
01:16:10,583 --> 01:16:12,783
Hello, Tom.
Neither rain nor wind nor snow.

969
01:16:12,983 --> 01:16:14,983
That's the mailman. O'Doole here?

970
01:16:21,483 --> 01:16:24,283
Hello, O'Doole.
You don't look happy.

971
01:16:24,483 --> 01:16:26,483
Look at this mess.

972
01:16:26,683 --> 01:16:29,883
Guttin' the golden calf again.
I don't know whether to laugh or cry.

973
01:16:30,083 --> 01:16:33,683
Yeah, it's awful confusing.
You know a yegg
named DropJohnson?

974
01:16:33,883 --> 01:16:36,483
- We spanked him
a couple of times.
- Where does he flop?

975
01:16:36,683 --> 01:16:38,783
- Terminal Hotel, Bay Street.

976
01:16:38,983 --> 01:16:43,183
Jesus!
Look, don't nobody ask me since
I'm just the chief around here,

977
01:16:43,483 --> 01:16:45,483
but I'll tell you my opinion.

978
01:16:45,683 --> 01:16:49,783
Caspar is just as crazy as Leo,
and an "eye-tie"
into the bargain.

979
01:16:50,083 --> 01:16:53,083
What's the matter, O'Doole?
Doesn't anything ever suit you?

980
01:17:03,283 --> 01:17:05,983
Hop in, Tom.
We been lookin'for you.

981
01:17:06,283 --> 01:17:08,583
- I'm busy.
- Hop in anyway.

982
01:17:08,783 --> 01:17:11,883
You can't hijack me, Tic-Tac.
We're on the same side now.

983
01:17:12,083 --> 01:17:14,783
Or didn't you get
that far in school?

984
01:17:24,183 --> 01:17:25,983
How'd you get the fat lip?

985
01:17:26,183 --> 01:17:30,383
- Old war wound.
Acts up around morons.
- Very smart.

986
01:17:30,583 --> 01:17:33,583
What were you doing
at the club, talking
things over with Leo?

987
01:17:33,783 --> 01:17:36,583
Don't think so hard, Eddie.
You might sprain something.

988
01:17:36,783 --> 01:17:39,383
You are so goddamn smart.

989
01:17:39,583 --> 01:17:41,383
Except you ain't.

990
01:17:41,583 --> 01:17:44,383
I get you, smart guy.
I know what you are.

991
01:17:44,583 --> 01:17:46,483
Straight as a corkscrew.

992
01:17:46,583 --> 01:17:48,483
Mr. Inside Out-ski,

993
01:17:48,583 --> 01:17:52,583
like some goddamn Bolshevik
picking up his orders
from Yegg Central.

994
01:17:52,883 --> 01:17:54,883
You think you're
so goddamn smart.

995
01:17:55,083 --> 01:17:57,183
You join upJohnny Caspar,

996
01:17:57,283 --> 01:17:59,283
you bump Bernie Bernbaum.

997
01:18:00,583 --> 01:18:03,883
Up is down. Black is white.

998
01:18:05,283 --> 01:18:08,283
Well, I think you're half smart.

999
01:18:08,383 --> 01:18:10,883
I think you were straight
with your frail,

1000
01:18:11,083 --> 01:18:13,583
I think you were queer
with Johnny Caspar...

1001
01:18:13,783 --> 01:18:17,783
and I think you'd sooner
join a ladies' league
than gun a guy down.

1002
01:18:18,083 --> 01:18:22,283
Then I hear from these
two geniuses they never even
saw this rub-out take place.

1003
01:18:22,583 --> 01:18:26,183
- Boss said to have him do it.
He didn't say nothing about--
- Shut up!

1004
01:18:26,483 --> 01:18:29,583
Or maybe you still got
too many teeth.

1005
01:18:32,283 --> 01:18:36,283
Everyone is so goddamn smart.

1006
01:18:36,583 --> 01:18:40,183
Well, we'll go out
to Miller's Crossing...

1007
01:18:40,283 --> 01:18:43,183
and we'll see who's smart.

1008
01:19:07,483 --> 01:19:11,583
You understand if we don't
find a stiff out here,
we leave a fresh one.

1009
01:19:28,683 --> 01:19:31,483
Where are your friends
when you need 'em, huh?

1010
01:19:32,883 --> 01:19:35,183
Where's Leo now?

1011
01:19:37,283 --> 01:19:39,583
Hey, Tic-Tac!

1012
01:19:39,783 --> 01:19:43,483
You ever notice how
the snappy dialogue dries up...

1013
01:19:43,583 --> 01:19:46,083
once a guy starts
soiling his union suit?

1014
01:20:30,083 --> 01:20:34,183
Okay. There's nothing out here.

1015
01:20:47,383 --> 01:20:51,983
- Think about this... smart guy.

1016
01:20:52,183 --> 01:20:54,983
It's hanky time.

1017
01:20:59,883 --> 01:21:03,083
- Birds have been at him.

1018
01:21:03,283 --> 01:21:05,683
Jesus Christ.

1019
01:21:30,483 --> 01:21:34,283
Told you
to put one in his brain,
not in his stinkin' face!

1020
01:21:38,383 --> 01:21:41,983
I told you, Dane.
We heard two shots.

1021
01:22:09,683 --> 01:22:11,683
Hello, Drop.

1022
01:22:15,483 --> 01:22:17,783
How are the Katzenjammers?

1023
01:22:17,983 --> 01:22:20,583
Hello, Tom. What's the rumpus?

1024
01:22:22,083 --> 01:22:24,183
Had any visitors?

1025
01:22:24,383 --> 01:22:26,383
Uhh, no.

1026
01:22:26,583 --> 01:22:28,383
Not ever, Drop?

1027
01:22:28,483 --> 01:22:30,383
Not lately.

1028
01:22:30,583 --> 01:22:32,983
Then you must be happy to see me.

1029
01:22:36,383 --> 01:22:38,183
So, uh...

1030
01:22:38,383 --> 01:22:42,083
you didn't see Bernie Bernbaum
before he was shown across.

1031
01:22:42,283 --> 01:22:44,183
Uh, no.

1032
01:22:44,383 --> 01:22:46,283
Seen him since?

1033
01:22:48,583 --> 01:22:50,783
One last question, Drop.

1034
01:22:50,983 --> 01:22:55,383
You got a lot of money
on tomorrow's fight.

1035
01:22:55,683 --> 01:22:59,583
That your bet, or, uh...
you placing it for a friend?

1036
01:22:59,783 --> 01:23:01,683
No, no, no, it's my bet.

1037
01:23:01,783 --> 01:23:06,283
- I just have a good feeling
about that fight.
- A good feeling, huh?

1038
01:23:06,583 --> 01:23:09,083
When did a feeling
return to your head?

1039
01:23:09,283 --> 01:23:11,783
You've outgrown that one.

1040
01:23:11,983 --> 01:23:14,083
Must be all the thinking
you been doing.

1041
01:23:14,283 --> 01:23:17,183
Tell Bernie something's come up,
he has to get in touch.

1042
01:23:17,483 --> 01:23:20,383
There'll be nothing stirring
till I talk to him.

1043
01:23:52,783 --> 01:23:57,783
All right, anyone left in there,
come on out grabbing air.
You know the drill.

1044
01:24:13,883 --> 01:24:16,483
Aah!

1045
01:24:59,183 --> 01:25:01,983
Hello, Tom.
Where you been hiding?

1046
01:25:02,183 --> 01:25:04,383
Hither and yon.
Is the mayor in?

1047
01:25:04,483 --> 01:25:06,883
- He's with Mr. Caspar.
- That's who I'm looking for.

1048
01:25:07,083 --> 01:25:10,183
- Scare me up some gargle, will you?
- Sure. I'll announce you.

1049
01:25:10,283 --> 01:25:12,983
Don't bother. I'm well-liked.

1050
01:25:14,783 --> 01:25:17,783
I can't do it.
I'll look ridiculous.
It simply isn't done.

1051
01:25:17,983 --> 01:25:20,883
-Assistants, maybe.
- For a mayor, you don't hear so hot.

1052
01:25:21,083 --> 01:25:23,983
I said head.
Head of the assessor's office.

1053
01:25:24,183 --> 01:25:28,183
- But there are two of them.
- I can count. Co-heads.

1054
01:25:28,483 --> 01:25:31,383
Johnny, needless to say,
this office will do
anything in its power...

1055
01:25:31,583 --> 01:25:34,083
to assist you and your cousins.

1056
01:25:34,283 --> 01:25:35,783
We did it for Leo, of course,
on countless occasions.

1057
01:25:35,883 --> 01:25:37,883
We did it for Leo, of course,
on countless occasions.

1058
01:25:37,983 --> 01:25:41,783
Damn right.
Had every potato-eater from
County Cork on the public tit.

1059
01:25:41,983 --> 01:25:44,283
But there's a way we do things,

1060
01:25:44,483 --> 01:25:47,483
hallowed by usage
and consecrated by time.

1061
01:25:47,783 --> 01:25:52,683
- When we put people on the pad
when Leo was running things--
- Leo ain't runnin' things!

1062
01:25:52,883 --> 01:25:57,183
I ain't interested
in ancient history!
I'm runnin'things now!

1063
01:25:57,383 --> 01:25:59,783
Nobody can appreciate it
more than I.

1064
01:25:59,983 --> 01:26:02,183
I can give them jobs.
I can give them good jobs.

1065
01:26:02,383 --> 01:26:05,383
I can even give them jobs
where they won't have
to perform any work,

1066
01:26:05,583 --> 01:26:08,283
where their lack of English
will be no impediment, but I can't--

1067
01:26:08,383 --> 01:26:10,583
What is this, the high hat?

1068
01:26:10,783 --> 01:26:15,783
Tom, can you explain it to him?
I can put them in public works,
but I can't--

1069
01:26:16,083 --> 01:26:17,883
You can do whatever
the hell Caspar tells you.

1070
01:26:18,083 --> 01:26:20,483
I don't remember
all this double talk
when Leo gave you an order.

1071
01:26:20,583 --> 01:26:24,683
- Tom.Jesus!
- Stop whimpering
and do as you're told.

1072
01:26:24,983 --> 01:26:28,083
- You can start
by gettin'out of here.
-Johnny, it's my office.

1073
01:26:28,183 --> 01:26:32,983
Get out of here!
Take it on the heel and toe
before I whack you one!

1074
01:26:35,483 --> 01:26:37,783
- You two beat it.

1075
01:26:37,883 --> 01:26:41,883
-
- Yeah, go and keep
the mayor company.

1076
01:26:42,183 --> 01:26:45,083
I'll take care
of ya's later.

1077
01:26:54,683 --> 01:26:57,483
- Runnin' things--
it ain't all gravy.

1078
01:26:57,783 --> 01:27:01,683
- What's the fireworks?
-Knocking over one of Leo's clubs.

1079
01:27:01,883 --> 01:27:04,883
Son of a bitch
won't go belly up.

1080
01:27:05,183 --> 01:27:08,183
I'm sorry, kid.
I heard about your
little ride this morning.

1081
01:27:08,383 --> 01:27:10,183
Yeah, well,
sorry don't fix things.

1082
01:27:10,383 --> 01:27:14,083
We could just as easily
have missed Bernie's corpse,
and I'd be dead now.

1083
01:27:14,183 --> 01:27:17,783
I know, I know, but that don't mean
the Dane's up to anything.

1084
01:27:18,083 --> 01:27:21,783
So he hears a rumor
that Bernie ain't dead.
These stories pop up.

1085
01:27:21,983 --> 01:27:25,083
Any stories
about Bernie being alive
the Dane's made up himself.

1086
01:27:25,283 --> 01:27:28,983
You don't know that.
It don't make sense. Why would he?

1087
01:27:29,283 --> 01:27:31,583
There could be
a damn good reason...

1088
01:27:33,383 --> 01:27:36,083
if you got
a fixed fight coming up.

1089
01:27:38,483 --> 01:27:41,483
- Do you?
- Maybe.

1090
01:27:43,283 --> 01:27:47,183
Okay, yeah, sure.
Tomorrow night.
The fix is in. What of it?

1091
01:27:47,383 --> 01:27:49,583
- The Dane know about it?
- Yeah.

1092
01:27:53,483 --> 01:27:55,983
Okay, I get it.

1093
01:27:56,183 --> 01:27:58,983
If the Dane's been selling
you out on these fights
and means to again,

1094
01:27:59,183 --> 01:28:02,183
- he's gonna have to have somebody
else to point the finger at.
- Yeah, I get it.

1095
01:28:02,383 --> 01:28:04,683
With Bernie dead,
there ain't a hell of a lot
of people he can point to.

1096
01:28:04,883 --> 01:28:08,483
Yeah, the Dane sells me out,
makes pretend Bernie's still
doing it.

1097
01:28:08,683 --> 01:28:10,583
That's real pretty.

1098
01:28:10,783 --> 01:28:14,683
Bernie leaked the fix,
and you take the fall
for not killing him.

1099
01:28:16,883 --> 01:28:21,183
But I don't know.
Why would Eddie cross me
like that? Money?

1100
01:28:21,383 --> 01:28:23,583
Okay, everybody likes money,

1101
01:28:23,683 --> 01:28:26,783
but somehow it just
don't seem like him.

1102
01:28:26,983 --> 01:28:31,283
- And I know the Dane.
- Nobody knows anybody.
Not that well.

1103
01:28:31,583 --> 01:28:34,183
Money don't mean
that much to him.

1104
01:28:34,383 --> 01:28:36,483
Then it's not just
the money he's after.

1105
01:28:36,683 --> 01:28:40,283
- He's got a wart on his fanny.
- Huh?

1106
01:28:40,483 --> 01:28:43,983
A wart on his fanny
giving him the fidgets.

1107
01:28:44,083 --> 01:28:46,483
Maybe he's sick of sitting
on the couch.

1108
01:28:46,683 --> 01:28:49,783
Maybe behind your desk
don't look like a bad place to move to.

1109
01:28:49,883 --> 01:28:52,283
Kid, you got a lip on you.

1110
01:28:53,583 --> 01:28:55,883
But you're honest.

1111
01:28:56,083 --> 01:28:59,583
That's something we can't
get enough of in this business.

1112
01:29:03,283 --> 01:29:06,583
I'll admit since last we jawed...

1113
01:29:06,883 --> 01:29:09,183
my stomach's
been seizing up on me.

1114
01:29:09,283 --> 01:29:12,183
If the Dane's saying
we should double-cross you--

1115
01:29:12,283 --> 01:29:16,383
You double-cross once,
where's it all end?

1116
01:29:16,683 --> 01:29:19,383
An interesting ethical question.

1117
01:29:24,883 --> 01:29:27,983
I'll find the Dane,
talk to him,
straighten things out.

1118
01:29:28,283 --> 01:29:31,583
- Sure, talk to him.
Have a chat.
- I'll take care of it.

1119
01:29:31,683 --> 01:29:34,683
- Ask him if he's selling you out.
I'm sure he'll come clean.
- I'll take care of it.

1120
01:29:34,883 --> 01:29:38,283
- You're swimmin' in it.
- I said I'd take care of it!

1121
01:29:47,983 --> 01:29:51,383
-Johnny.

1122
01:29:51,483 --> 01:29:55,683
My chin's hanging out
right alongside yours.

1123
01:29:57,583 --> 01:30:00,883
I'd worry a lot less if
I thought you were worrying enough.

1124
01:30:05,483 --> 01:30:07,283
But I am, kid.

1125
01:30:11,083 --> 01:30:12,883
Christ.

1126
01:30:14,283 --> 01:30:16,583
Running things.

1127
01:30:26,983 --> 01:30:29,283
- Yeah?
I got your message.

1128
01:30:29,483 --> 01:30:32,483
Oh, Bernie. I had a dream
about you the other day.

1129
01:30:32,683 --> 01:30:35,983
- Yeah? A nightmare?
- On the contrary. Very sweet.

1130
01:30:36,283 --> 01:30:39,383
I dreamt you were
lying out at Miller's Crossing
with your face blown off.

1131
01:30:39,583 --> 01:30:42,883
You get a kick out of that?
- I was in stitches.

1132
01:30:43,183 --> 01:30:45,883
- It's Mink, isn't it?
- I came back.
He wasn't happy to see me.

1133
01:30:46,083 --> 01:30:47,883
- Can you beat that?
- Some friend.

1134
01:30:48,083 --> 01:30:49,983
Yeah. You know what
a nervous boy he was.

1135
01:30:49,983 --> 01:30:53,683
I figured you're a friend,
maybe you could use
some insurance.

1136
01:30:53,983 --> 01:30:55,883
Did Mink have a .22?

1137
01:30:58,083 --> 01:31:00,983
-He already ditched it. Why?
- After he shot Rug?

1138
01:31:01,083 --> 01:31:04,183
- Yeah. How'd you know?
- Doesn't matter.

1139
01:31:04,283 --> 01:31:08,883
- I've been thinking about
our deal. You can stick it
in your ear.  - Huh?

1140
01:31:09,083 --> 01:31:12,383
You don't have anything
on me that I don't have on you,
so I'm calling your bluff.

1141
01:31:12,683 --> 01:31:14,883
- Wait a minute.
- I'm pulling out
tomorrow morning.

1142
01:31:14,983 --> 01:31:18,483
You only have to decide
whether or not I leave behind
a message for Caspar...

1143
01:31:18,683 --> 01:31:20,483
that you're still around.

1144
01:31:20,683 --> 01:31:22,983
If you want me to keep
my mouth shut, it's gonna
cost you some dough.

1145
01:31:23,183 --> 01:31:25,683
I figure a thousand bucks
is reasonable, so I want two.

1146
01:31:25,783 --> 01:31:28,883
- In a pig's eye!
- I'm going out. I'll be back
at 4:00 this morning.

1147
01:31:29,183 --> 01:31:31,983
If you're not here at my place,
4:00, with the dough,

1148
01:31:32,183 --> 01:31:35,383
- Caspar's gonna be
looking for you tomorrow.
- Wait, wait, wait!

1149
01:31:43,283 --> 01:31:46,583
- Got any money?
- No.

1150
01:31:48,083 --> 01:31:50,383
Okay.

1151
01:32:04,783 --> 01:32:06,683
Third race tonight.

1152
01:32:06,783 --> 01:32:10,483
By the finish, Tailor Made
had a view of the field.

1153
01:32:10,783 --> 01:32:13,083
You oughta lay off
the ponies, Tom.

1154
01:32:19,783 --> 01:32:21,583
Okay.

1155
01:32:27,983 --> 01:32:31,383
Lazarre said he's sorry about this.
It's just getting out of hand.

1156
01:32:31,583 --> 01:32:33,483
Yeah.

1157
01:32:33,583 --> 01:32:35,483
He likes you, Tom.

1158
01:32:35,683 --> 01:32:38,083
He said we didn't have to
break anything.

1159
01:32:38,983 --> 01:32:41,083
It's okay.

1160
01:32:41,183 --> 01:32:43,683
Tell him there's
no hard feelings. Heh!

1161
01:32:43,883 --> 01:32:47,883
Christ, Tom...
he knows that.

1162
01:32:50,683 --> 01:32:52,783
Take care now.

1163
01:33:07,183 --> 01:33:09,083
- Tom Reagan.
- Yes, sir.

1164
01:33:09,183 --> 01:33:12,683
- Mr. Caspar's in the great room.
- Swell. Can you hold these?

1165
01:33:14,383 --> 01:33:16,283
Kid, what's the rumpus?

1166
01:33:16,483 --> 01:33:18,283
I got news.

1167
01:33:18,483 --> 01:33:21,483
Yeah. News at this end too.

1168
01:33:21,683 --> 01:33:24,083
My stomach's been
seizing up on me.

1169
01:33:24,183 --> 01:33:26,783
- Mink just told me that he--
- Eh?

1170
01:33:26,983 --> 01:33:30,383
- You talked to Mink?
- Yeah, on the phone.

1171
01:33:30,583 --> 01:33:33,583
The Dane wants you to think
that he's disappeared
so you can't talk to him,

1172
01:33:33,783 --> 01:33:36,683
- but he's been here in town.
- You sure it was Mink?

1173
01:33:36,883 --> 01:33:40,583
Yeah. See for yourself.
He's coming to my place,
4:00 this morning.

1174
01:33:40,883 --> 01:33:44,483
He's afraid of
a crossing with Dane.
He told me about the fix.

1175
01:33:44,683 --> 01:33:47,883
He says he'll sing for
a couple of grand skip money,
tell us everyone involved.

1176
01:33:48,183 --> 01:33:50,483
But you'd better take care
of the Dane tonight.

1177
01:33:50,683 --> 01:33:53,383
Mink says he's
coming after us tonight.

1178
01:33:59,583 --> 01:34:01,983
Leo's holed up
at Whiskey Nick's dump.

1179
01:34:02,183 --> 01:34:04,083
What? How do you know?

1180
01:34:04,083 --> 01:34:07,083
That ain't all we know, smart guy.

1181
01:34:08,383 --> 01:34:11,483
Recognize your playmate?

1182
01:34:15,683 --> 01:34:18,383
You thought I'd quit, huh? Uh-uh.

1183
01:34:18,583 --> 01:34:21,383
I followed you
this afternoon,

1184
01:34:21,683 --> 01:34:25,183
and I wondered why Einstein
would wanna talk to a gorilla.

1185
01:34:25,283 --> 01:34:28,683
So I grabbed the gorilla,
and I beat it out of him.

1186
01:34:28,983 --> 01:34:32,383
You give me a big guy
every time. They break easy.
Not like you.

1187
01:34:32,583 --> 01:34:35,883
Is there a point,
or are you just brushing up
on your small talk?

1188
01:34:36,183 --> 01:34:39,483
I like that.
Cool under fire.

1189
01:34:40,783 --> 01:34:42,683
I'm impressed.

1190
01:34:44,383 --> 01:34:47,883
The gorilla didn't know
whose stiff we found,
but I can fill that in.

1191
01:34:48,083 --> 01:34:50,983
You killed Mink,
you son of a bitch!

1192
01:34:52,283 --> 01:34:55,583
It was Mink,
you son of a bitch.

1193
01:34:55,883 --> 01:35:00,483
It was Mink, and by God,
I'll hear you say it.

1194
01:35:00,783 --> 01:35:03,083
Is this how you told Drop
his story?

1195
01:35:05,483 --> 01:35:07,683
Come here, bum.

1196
01:35:11,483 --> 01:35:14,583
I am gonna send you
to a deep, dark place,

1197
01:35:14,783 --> 01:35:17,483
and I am gonna have fun doing it.

1198
01:35:33,983 --> 01:35:35,883
Oof!.

1199
01:35:36,083 --> 01:35:41,083
You son of a bitch!
Son of a bitch!
You lousy son of a bitch!

1200
01:35:41,483 --> 01:35:45,083
If there's one thing
I can't stand,
it's a double-cross artist!

1201
01:35:47,683 --> 01:35:50,583
I had a theory
about this son of a bitch!

1202
01:35:54,983 --> 01:35:59,683
Shut up, you lousy
son of a bitch, or I'll give you
something to holler about!

1203
01:35:59,983 --> 01:36:02,983
Johnny, it's okay.
The Dane made him do it.
It's not important.

1204
01:36:03,283 --> 01:36:06,683
Then make him shut it!

1205
01:36:06,883 --> 01:36:10,583
And we do the same to Mink
this very same night!

1206
01:36:10,783 --> 01:36:13,583
We can't double-cross Mink.
He wants to spill the whole setup.

1207
01:36:13,783 --> 01:36:17,283
- I've never let
a son of a bitch walk.
- You've never crossed anyone.

1208
01:36:17,483 --> 01:36:20,783
4:00, my place. Mink's
coming in on his own hook,
so I promised him the money.

1209
01:36:21,083 --> 01:36:26,183
- Don't make me out
to be a liar.

1210
01:36:28,883 --> 01:36:31,283
Look at this, kid.

1211
01:36:33,083 --> 01:36:35,883
Something I try to teach
all my boys.

1212
01:36:45,583 --> 01:36:48,383
Always put one in the brain.

1213
01:37:10,283 --> 01:37:12,083
What's the rumpus?

1214
01:37:12,283 --> 01:37:15,683
I was just in the neighborhood
feeling a little daffy.

1215
01:37:15,983 --> 01:37:18,183
- What are you doing?
- Walking.

1216
01:37:18,283 --> 01:37:20,483
Don't let on more
than you have to.

1217
01:37:20,683 --> 01:37:22,483
In the rain.

1218
01:37:27,183 --> 01:37:29,083
Bernie's dead, isn't he?

1219
01:37:30,483 --> 01:37:33,483
- What makes you think that?
- That's no answer.

1220
01:37:38,283 --> 01:37:40,883
I can't tell you
anything yet.

1221
01:37:41,083 --> 01:37:43,883
No one really cares, do they?

1222
01:37:43,983 --> 01:37:48,983
- His friends
didn't really like him.
- He didn't like his friends.

1223
01:37:49,183 --> 01:37:52,283
You're someone to talk.
You're a son of a bitch, Tom.

1224
01:37:52,583 --> 01:37:55,383
You got me
to tell you where he was,
and then you killed him.

1225
01:37:56,683 --> 01:37:58,683
I want to know why.

1226
01:37:58,783 --> 01:38:02,483
- What was in it for you?
- Nothing for me.

1227
01:38:07,083 --> 01:38:10,683
Giving up Bernie was
the only way I could see to
straighten things out for Leo.

1228
01:38:12,783 --> 01:38:15,583
I thought you said
you didn't care about Leo.

1229
01:38:15,783 --> 01:38:19,283
I said we were through.
It's not the same thing.

1230
01:38:19,583 --> 01:38:21,983
I don't understand.
I don't care.

1231
01:38:22,183 --> 01:38:25,383
I don't care what reasons you had
or you thought you had.

1232
01:38:25,483 --> 01:38:27,983
He's still alive.

1233
01:38:30,183 --> 01:38:32,183
You expect me to believe you?

1234
01:38:37,583 --> 01:38:39,483
No.

1235
01:38:42,783 --> 01:38:45,783
That's you all over, Tom.

1236
01:38:46,083 --> 01:38:48,383
A lie and no heart.

1237
01:39:06,283 --> 01:39:08,183
Oh--

1238
01:39:15,783 --> 01:39:17,783
It isn't easy, is it, Verna?

1239
01:39:33,483 --> 01:39:37,283
But before
you even think about doing
that, you gotta towel down.

1240
01:39:37,483 --> 01:39:42,783
So you towel down first
with a hot towel,
as hot as you can stand.

1241
01:39:42,983 --> 01:39:45,483
Put the razor
in cold water, not hot,

1242
01:39:45,683 --> 01:39:48,283
because metal
does what in cold?

1243
01:39:48,583 --> 01:39:52,783
- I don't know,Johnny.
- That's why I'm telling you!
It contracts.

1244
01:39:55,083 --> 01:39:58,783
That way you get
a first-class shave every time.

1245
01:39:59,083 --> 01:40:00,983
Okay,Johnny.

1246
01:40:03,683 --> 01:40:05,683
Ain't it the life though?

1247
01:40:09,383 --> 01:40:12,783
Hello, Sal. You can dangle.

1248
01:40:13,083 --> 01:40:17,683
Hello, Tom. You sure?
You don't look so hot.

1249
01:40:17,983 --> 01:40:19,683
I'm okay.

1250
01:40:22,483 --> 01:40:24,583
I'll drive him home.

1251
01:41:17,183 --> 01:41:19,883
Mr. Reagan, there were shots.

1252
01:41:20,083 --> 01:41:22,883
Go down to the drug store
and call the police.

1253
01:41:24,683 --> 01:41:27,483
You'd better stay there
till the officers arrive.

1254
01:41:28,683 --> 01:41:30,683
Will my cats be all right?

1255
01:41:30,783 --> 01:41:32,783
Yeah, they'll be fine.

1256
01:42:24,683 --> 01:42:27,583
I get it. You set me up.

1257
01:42:27,683 --> 01:42:30,583
Anything to avoid
a little dirty work yourself, huh?

1258
01:42:32,783 --> 01:42:35,983
How'd you know he'd get it
and not me? Or didn't you care?

1259
01:42:36,283 --> 01:42:38,683
I figured you'd come early
looking for blood.

1260
01:42:38,883 --> 01:42:41,683
He wouldn't, so you'd likely
have the drop on him.

1261
01:42:43,383 --> 01:42:47,483
You're right.
The chump never knew what hit him.

1262
01:42:47,583 --> 01:42:50,983
But if you knew
I'd come to kill you,
how do you know I won't still?

1263
01:42:51,183 --> 01:42:54,083
There's nothing in it
for you now.

1264
01:42:54,283 --> 01:42:57,083
With him dead, you and me
got nothing on each other.

1265
01:42:58,183 --> 01:43:00,583
- Let me have the gun.
- Why?

1266
01:43:00,783 --> 01:43:03,183
Pin this on the Dane.

1267
01:43:03,283 --> 01:43:06,183
Neither of us want him
walking around after this.

1268
01:43:06,383 --> 01:43:09,983
The cops'll be Leo's now.
They won't care what
they hang the Dane for.

1269
01:43:10,183 --> 01:43:12,083
I guess that's true,

1270
01:43:12,283 --> 01:43:16,483
if you don't mind keeping
the gun that killed Caspar
and Mink.

1271
01:43:17,683 --> 01:43:19,983
Why did Mink
shoot Rug anyway?

1272
01:43:20,183 --> 01:43:22,083
I don't know.
It was just a mix-up.

1273
01:43:22,283 --> 01:43:24,583
Here.

1274
01:43:27,483 --> 01:43:31,083
- So you're gonna say
the Dane did this?
- Sure.

1275
01:43:31,283 --> 01:43:33,983
Mink thought Rug
was tailing him.

1276
01:43:34,183 --> 01:43:36,683
You know Mink. Hysterical.
Skin full of hop,
head full of boogeymen.

1277
01:43:36,883 --> 01:43:41,183
Comes home crying one day,
saying he had to pop
one of the Dane's spies.

1278
01:43:41,483 --> 01:43:44,883
Rug was tailing Verna,
not Mink. Mink just
happened to be with her.

1279
01:43:45,083 --> 01:43:46,983
Funny, ain't it?

1280
01:43:47,083 --> 01:43:50,183
Mink was terrified
the Dane'd find out me and him
were jungled up together.

1281
01:43:50,383 --> 01:43:53,283
I bet you kept him
worried about that to
keep him under your thumb.

1282
01:43:53,583 --> 01:43:55,883
Yeah, so what?
Scratch, huh?

1283
01:43:56,083 --> 01:43:58,583
A little bonus.

1284
01:43:58,683 --> 01:44:01,983
- Why did Mink take Rug's hair?
- Beats me. The kid was dizzy.

1285
01:44:02,183 --> 01:44:06,183
Fifty-fifty on the dough?
Or maybe I should get more,
since I did the deed.

1286
01:44:08,883 --> 01:44:11,583
Okay, you keep it.
I want you to have it.

1287
01:44:18,483 --> 01:44:23,083
Bernie... we can't pin this
on the Dane.

1288
01:44:23,283 --> 01:44:28,883
- Why not?
- Because the Dane's already
dead halfway across town.

1289
01:44:29,183 --> 01:44:32,283
- What the hell
are you talking about?
- Eddie Dane is dead.

1290
01:44:32,583 --> 01:44:34,383
It's gotta be you.

1291
01:44:36,083 --> 01:44:38,383
I mean, it was your gun.

1292
01:44:40,783 --> 01:44:44,783
What is this?
What the hell are you talking about?

1293
01:44:45,083 --> 01:44:47,383
You--

1294
01:44:47,583 --> 01:44:50,983
You took my gun.
It's just your word against mine.

1295
01:44:54,483 --> 01:44:56,583
Not necessarily.

1296
01:44:57,683 --> 01:44:59,783
Are you crazy?

1297
01:44:59,983 --> 01:45:03,183
We're square.
You said it yourself.
We got nothing on each other.

1298
01:45:03,383 --> 01:45:05,683
Yep.

1299
01:45:05,783 --> 01:45:10,083
So what's in it for you?
There's no angle.

1300
01:45:10,283 --> 01:45:13,083
You can't just shoot me
like that.

1301
01:45:16,683 --> 01:45:20,083
Jesus Christ,
it don't make sense.

1302
01:45:22,383 --> 01:45:24,283
Tommy--

1303
01:45:26,283 --> 01:45:28,783
Tommy!

1304
01:45:30,583 --> 01:45:32,483
Look in your heart.

1305
01:45:35,083 --> 01:45:37,683
- Look in your heart.
- What heart?

1306
01:46:22,883 --> 01:46:24,883
Tad? It's Tom.

1307
01:46:26,383 --> 01:46:29,283
Tell Lazarre
I got his money.

1308
01:46:29,483 --> 01:46:31,383
Yeah, all of it.

1309
01:46:31,583 --> 01:46:34,383
I wanna place a bet
on tonight's fight.

1310
01:46:39,483 --> 01:46:41,283
- They set you up downstairs?
- How's that?

1311
01:46:41,483 --> 01:46:43,583
A little hooch, whatever?

1312
01:46:43,683 --> 01:46:46,483
Thanks for coming, Tom.
Leo's real anxious to see you.

1313
01:46:46,683 --> 01:46:48,683
Yeah, I happened to be near.

1314
01:46:51,083 --> 01:46:54,183
Well, uh, actually this might
not be the best time.

1315
01:46:54,383 --> 01:46:57,183
- Who's he got in there?
- O'Doole and the mayor.

1316
01:46:57,383 --> 01:47:01,883
- I'll try again.
- They're planting the sheeny
tomorrow. You could stop by.

1317
01:47:31,283 --> 01:47:34,783
- Big turnout.
- Drop dead.

1318
01:47:34,983 --> 01:47:36,983
She's under a lot of strain.

1319
01:47:37,183 --> 01:47:40,583
- Yeah, well, at least
she didn't hit me.

1320
01:47:40,683 --> 01:47:43,983
Glad you came, Tommy.

1321
01:47:44,183 --> 01:47:47,883
- I guess, uh-- Huh?
- She's taking the car.

1322
01:47:52,683 --> 01:47:55,683
- I guess we're walkin'.
- Guess we are.

1323
01:48:00,783 --> 01:48:02,883
We're, uh--
We're getting married.

1324
01:48:05,783 --> 01:48:08,183
Congratulations.

1325
01:48:08,383 --> 01:48:13,383
Funny thing is, she asked me to
tie the knot. I guess you're
not supposed to say that.

1326
01:48:13,683 --> 01:48:16,383
- It doesn't matter.
Congratulations.
- Thanks.

1327
01:48:17,983 --> 01:48:20,783
Hell, Tom, why didn't you
tell me what you were up to?

1328
01:48:20,883 --> 01:48:23,283
I thought you'd
really gone over.

1329
01:48:23,383 --> 01:48:26,883
Not that I didn't deserve it,
but you could've told me.

1330
01:48:27,083 --> 01:48:30,483
Telling you would only
have queered things if it--

1331
01:48:30,783 --> 01:48:33,583
There just wasn't any point.

1332
01:48:33,783 --> 01:48:35,583
I can see that.

1333
01:48:37,183 --> 01:48:40,083
It was a smart play all around.

1334
01:48:40,283 --> 01:48:43,183
I guess you know I'm grateful.

1335
01:48:43,383 --> 01:48:45,283
No need.

1336
01:48:47,083 --> 01:48:49,783
Heh!
I guess you picked
that fight with me...

1337
01:48:49,983 --> 01:48:53,283
just to check yourself
in with Caspar.

1338
01:48:53,383 --> 01:48:57,083
I don't know.
Do you always know
why you do things, Leo?

1339
01:48:57,383 --> 01:48:59,183
Sure I do.

1340
01:49:01,383 --> 01:49:04,083
- It was a smart play.
- Fine.

1341
01:49:07,383 --> 01:49:10,783
Jesus, Tom, I'd do anything
if you'd work for me again.

1342
01:49:11,083 --> 01:49:14,283
I know I've made
some bonehead plays,
